Photo: Facebook Image 49 of 49 Texas-based My Fit Foods to close all U.S. stores 1 / 49 Back to Gallery Healthy prepared meals company My Fit Foods will be closing its stores nationwide.
The Texas-based business announced on its website that the closing comes after 10 years in business:
"Since 2006, My Fit Foods has been on a mission to make healthy eating easy and accessible for everyone. We've enjoyed getting to know you, and we are proud that we have made a difference in many of your lives."
ALSO GONE: Ryan Hildebrand's Triniti restaurant closes
The statement went on to apologize for the sudden shutdown, but did not offer a reason for its closing:
"It is with heavy heart that we announce the closure of all our stores. We know that you have depended upon us to support your healthy habits, and we are deeply sorry for any inconvenience our closure may have caused you. Thank your for your kind support these past years."
As of Sunday, several Houston and Dallas stores were reportedly already closed, and the company's Twitter account was taken offline.
The business also supplied many packaged meals to stores and businesses around the Houston area, including H-E-B.
A spokesperson for the company did not immediately respond to our request for comment.
